      <p><b>General information</b><br>
        Siena is in Toscana (Tuscany), a region of Italy, and one of the most 
        important historical areas of the whole world. The capital of Toscana 
        is Firenze (Florence), which is only 70 km away from Siena. </p>
      <p>Tours of Firenze and other historical sites in Toscana can be booked 
        at the conference (not included in the conference fee). For more information, 
        please have a look at the <a href="http://www.dis.uniroma1.it/%7Eicdt03/icdt_burs.html" target="_blank">ICDT 
        social program</a>. </p>
      <p><b>Hotel Accomodation</b><br>
        The organizing agency, Consulta Umbra, proposes different hotels at different 
        rates. you can check them at the link below:</p>
      <p align="center"><a href="http://www.consultaumbria.com/icdt2003/hotel.php" target="_blank"><b>Hotel 
        Info and Rates</b></a></p>
      <p><b>Social Dinner</b><br>
        Social dinner will be held in restaurant La Taverna di San Giuseppe, Via 
        G. Dupr&eacute; 132 (400m from Piazza del Campo).</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p><b>How to Reach Siena</b><br>
        It is possible to reach Siena by car, by bus or by train. In Siena there 
        is no airport, the closest ones are in Florence at Peretola (Amerigo Vespucci 
        Airport, 90 Km.) and in Pisa (Galileo Galilei Airport, 130 Km.). <br>
        <br>
        <i>By car</i> <br>
        Siena is 57 Km. south of the A1 motorway exit &quot;Firenze Certosa&quot; 
        (coming from north) and 32 Km. west of the A1 motorway exit &quot;Valdichiana 
        Bettolle - Sinalunga&quot; (coming from south) <br>
        <br>
        <i>By bus</i><br>
        Bus lines in Siena are from or to Florence, from or to Rome , from or 
        to Grosseto and from or to Arezzo. For further information about the bus 
        schedules visit the web page of <a href="http://www.lazzi.it/senaautolinee/" target="_blank">public 
        transport company</a> <br>
        <br>
        <i>By train</i><br>
        Visit the website of the <a href="http://www.trenitalia.it" target="_blank">Italian 
        railways</a> and choose your itinerary. The average duration of journeys 
        are respectively: Florence Santa Maria Novella 1h55min (change in Empoli), 
        Pisa Centrale 2h15min (change in Empoli), Roma Termini 3h20min (change 
        in Chiusi) <br>
        <br>
        <i>Arriving at Pisa airport</i><br>
        There is a railway station inside Galilieo Galilei Airport through which 
        you reach Pisa Central Station in 5 minutes. From there you can take the 
        train to Siena. It is also possible to book a taxi, the average duration 
        of the car journey from the gate to Siena downtown is about 1h20min, the 
        cost is about 130 Euros + taxes <br>
        <br>
        <i>Arriving at Florence airport (Amerigo Vespucci Airport)</i><br>
        You can reach Florence downtown in 20 minutes with the Sita/Ataf Service 
        &quot;Vola in Bus&quot;, 66 buses per day that every 30 minutes link the 
        Amerigo Vespucci Airport to Santa Maria Novella Railways Station. From 
        there you can take both the train or the bus to Siena. From the airport, 
        it is also possible to book a taxi, the average duration of the car journey 
        from the gate to Siena downtown is about 1h10min, and the cost is about 
        100 Euros + taxes <br>
        <br>
        <i>Arriving at Rome airport (Leonardo Da Vinci, Fiumicino)</i><br>
        From the airport, you can reach Roma Termini railway station where you 
        can take a train to Siena, or Roma Tiburtina railway station where you 
        can take a bus to Siena. It is also possible to book a taxi from the airport. 
        The average duration of the car journey from the Leonardo Da Vinci Airport 
        to Siena downtown is about 2h45min, and the cost is about 280 Euros + 
        taxes </p>
